bug.short_desc: [abrt] sssd-dbus: ldb_msg_find_element(): sssd_ifp killed by SIGSEGV

long_desc.thetext:
Description of problem: I ran D-Feet (the graphical D-BUS testing tool) and connected to org.freedesktop.sssd.infopipe.
I then attempted to use org.freedesktop.sssd.infopipe.Users.ListByName, passing it my full username (sgallagh) and a numeric value for the limit.
Instead of getting a response back from D-BUS, the sssd_ifp process crashed.
Version-Release number of selected component: sssd-dbus-1.13.4-2.fc24
Additional info: reporter: libreport-2.7.0 backtrace_rating: 4 cmdline: /usr/libexec/sssd/sssd_ifp --uid 0 --gid 0 --debug-to-files crash_function: ldb_msg_find_element executable: /usr/libexec/sssd/sssd_ifp global_pid: 8806 kernel: 4.5.3-300.fc24.x86_64 pkg_fingerprint: 73BD E983 81B4 6521 pkg_vendor: Fedora Project reproducible: Not sure how to reproduce the problem runlevel: N 5 type: CCpp uid: 0
Truncated backtrace: Thread no. 1 (10 frames) #0 ldb_msg_find_element at ../common/ldb_msg.c:51 #1 ldb_msg_find_ldb_val at ../common/ldb_msg.c:399 #2 ldb_msg_find_attr_as_string at ../common/ldb_msg.c:584 #3 ifp_users_build_path_from_msg at src/responder/ifp/ifp_users.c:42 #4 ifp_users_list_copy at src/responder/ifp/ifp_users.c:321 #5 ifp_users_list_by_name_done at src/responder/ifp/ifp_users.c:398 #6 _tevent_req_error at ../tevent_req.c:167 #7 cache_req_done at src/responder/common/responder_cache_req.c:1152 #8 _tevent_req_error at ../tevent_req.c:167 #9 cache_req_cache_done at src/responder/common/responder_cache_req.c:887

Looks like it's fixed in current master, probably by https://git.fedorahosted.org/cgit/sssd.git/commit/?id=e8474ac0be7e81c0ca54eb09e2fef42595602945 and https://git.fedorahosted.org/cgit/sssd.git/commit/?id=c30b7a1931211fdcae0564551a7625cc4f6dee9f
